According to police spokesperson, Lt-Col Moatshe Ngoepe, two suspects, aged 29 and 31-years-old, who are both the deceased’s younger brothers, were arrested and positively linked to the beheading of 40-year-old, Irene Mopai, on 26 February, Bosveld Review reports.
READ MORE: Brothers ‘arrested’ in Limpopo for allegedly beheading sister
Ngoepe added that subsequent to the arrest, the deceased’s head was recovered in the nearby bushes.
The suspects will appear before the Lulekani Magistrates’ Court in Limpopo today, on a charge of murder.
